Here's a simple HTML file that creates a chessboard scene with animated cheese pieces moving randomly at 1 frame per second. You can copy and paste the following code into a `.html` file and open it in your web browser to see the animation.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Animated Cheese Chessboard</title>
    <style>
        body {
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
            height: 100vh;
            background-color: #f0f0f0;
            margin: 0;
        }
        .chessboard {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(8, 50px);
            grid-template-rows: repeat(8, 50px);
            border: 2px solid #333;
        }
        .chessboard div {
            width: 50px;
            height: 50px;
        }
        .chessboard div:nth-child(odd) {
            background-color: #eee;
        }
        .chessboard div:nth-child(even) {
            background-color: #ddd;
        }
        .cheese {
            width: 40px;
            height: 40px;
            background-color: yellow;
            clip-path: polygon(50% 0%, 100% 100%, 0% 100%);
            position: absolute;
            transition: transform 0.5s;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="chessboard" id="chessboard"></div>
    <script>
        const chessboard = document.getElementById('chessboard');
        const cheeseCount = 5;
        const cheeses = [];

        // Create cheese pieces
        for (let i = 0; i < cheeseCount; i++) {
            const cheese = document.createElement('div');
            cheese.classList.add('cheese');
            chessboard.appendChild(cheese);
            cheeses.push(cheese);
        }

        // Function to move cheese pieces randomly
        function moveCheeses() {
            cheeses.forEach(cheese => {
                const randomX = Math.floor(Math.random() * 8) * 50;
                const randomY = Math.floor(Math.random() * 8) * 50;
                cheese.style.transform = `translate(${randomX}px, ${randomY}px)`;
            });
        }

        // Move cheeses every second
        setInterval(moveCheeses, 1000);
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

### Explanation:
- **HTML Structure**: The chessboard is created using a `div` with a class of `chessboard`, which is styled as a grid.
- **CSS Styles**: The chessboard is styled with alternating colors for the squares, and the cheese pieces are styled as yellow triangles using the `clip-path` property.
- **JavaScript Logic**: The script creates a specified number of cheese pieces and moves them to random positions on the chessboard every second using `setInterval`.

You can adjust the number of cheese pieces by changing the `cheeseCount` variable in the JavaScript section. Enjoy your animated cheese chessboard!
